{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KDZC4LsWgzCivdQ6fbodXg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n\n1. The current certificate expires in about 1 day (Jun 23 to Jun 24 2026) - it's near-expiry as described.\n2. The TLS is mounted via the `rabbitmq-tls` secret (containing `tls.crt`, `tls.key`, `ca.crt`) at `/etc/rabbitmq/tls`.\n3. The CA key is in `rabbitmq-tls-ca` secret under key `ca.key`.\n4. There's an `openssl-toolbox` pod running that I can use to generate the new certificate.\n5. The SANs from the current cert include all the right DNS names, so I'll preserve those when generating the new leaf certificate.\n\nMy plan is to extract both the CA cert and key from their respective secrets, generate a new leaf certificate with 300+ days validity and the same SANs, then update the `rabbitmq-tls` secret with the new cert and key while keeping the CA cert unchanged. Since the secret is mounted as a volume, Kubernetes will automatically propagate the updates to the pods.\n\nHowever, RabbitMQ won't actually use the new certificate until the pods restart, so I'll need to do a rolling restart after updating the secret. Let me use the `openssl-toolbox` pod to generate the certificate, and first I'll examine what the CA cert looks like to understand the issuer details.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1458,"cache_read_input_tokens":48315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1458},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41d80bcc-c5fb-488c-b4dd-9558a6174ced","uuid":"b10d1325-c1d6-40c9-9f20-240c8bf91c57","request_id":"req_011CcLBfKqargbsN37UA2ZDC"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KDZC4LsWgzCivdQ6fbodXg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cert expires in 1 day. The secret `rabbitmq-tls` is volume-mounted at `/etc/rabbitmq/tls`. I'll generate a new 365-day leaf cert using the CA key from `rabbitmq-tls-ca`, update the secret, then rolling-restart the StatefulSet."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1458,"cache_read_input_tokens":48315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1458},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41d80bcc-c5fb-488c-b4dd-9558a6174ced","uuid":"ca0f0cf7-4898-41a6-84a6-f97ba6210a30","request_id":"req_011CcLBfKqargbsN37UA2ZDC"}
